commentTextItems.html: Demolition job from Odoyo as he takes out Hamilton's off stump. He missed with the cover drive and it's cost him his wicket. And he is followed back to the pavilion by the rest of the players and the drizzle persists.

commentPostTextItems.html: The umpires have stopped play for just now with Scotland one wicket down and hopefully this is only a shower. We will keep you posted
The covers and sheets are now being brought on by the ground staff
Unfortunately it is still raining here at Ayr and more sheets are going on the pitch and things don't look good but we will keep you posted.
It looks like the Scottish weather is winning once more and we're hearing the game has been called off with the raining still falling and running out of time. What a shame for all involved.
And I'm afraid to inform you that play has been canceled for the day for certain.
Hopefully we will have better luck for the second ODI tomorrow where you can join me Callum Stewart for more live updates and a ball-by-ball commentary.

commentTextItems.html: check drive from Watson is picked up at mid-off

commentPostTextItems.html: Very light rain and the umpires are having a chat but we're playing on here

commentTextItems.html: well timed drive towards the covers but a good stop in the field and no run
defended in to the ground
good yorker prevents a big hit and Hamilton guides it to cover and they run a quick single
front foot no ball gifts Hamilton a free hit
bottom edged from Watson but enough to get a single and picked up by third man
pulled away over midwicket and well-timed to reach the boundary
cut away passed point and easy running for a couple
